sql:
SELECT update_message, created_at
FROM system_updates
WHERE update_id > 1;

SELECT u.user_name, r.role_name, u.is_active
FROM users u
JOIN roles r ON u.role_id = r.role_id;

external_knowledge:
- Active participants refer to users with an 'is_active' status of 1; 
- Designated roles are those with an 'is_active' status of 1 and are linked to the user by 'role_id'; 
- Active connections are integrations with an 'is_active' status of 1 and are linked to the user through 'user_integration'.

sql:
SELECT user_name
FROM users
WHERE last_login >= (SELECT MAX(update_date) FROM system_updates);

SELECT COUNT(*) AS login_count
FROM user_activity
WHERE activity_type = 'login';

external_knowledge:
- 'content creators' are users with a specific role in the system;
- 'integrations' refer to external services or systems connected to the platform;
- 'permissions' are the actions or rights granted to a user based on their role.
